ingredient_details.name: Rayon
ingredient_details.description: Cellulose-based synthetic fiber commonly used in pad absorbent cores. Produced through chemical-intensive processes involving sodium hydroxide and carbon disulfide. Rayon can harbor bacteria and reduce vaginal moisture, potentially increasing toxic shock syndrome risk.

ingredient_details.name: Polyester
ingredient_details.description: Petroleum-derived plastic polymer used in pad backing and liners. Non-biodegradable and may release microplastics over time. Creates moisture-trapping barrier that prevents natural airflow and promotes yeast growth and bacterial overgrowth.

ingredient_details.name: Fragrance
ingredient_details.description: Synthetic fragrance compounds used to mask odors in period products. May contain undisclosed chemicals that can trigger allergic reactions, skin irritation, and reproductive health concerns. Studies suggest fragrance additives increase risk of vulvovaginal irritation and bacterial imbalance.

ingredient_details.name: Chlorine
ingredient_details.description: Bleaching agent used to whiten pad materials and improve absorbency. Creates toxic dioxin residues that persist in products. Chlorine exposure during manufacturing creates environmental hazards and consumer health risks through skin absorption.
